Reasoning: The paper deals with multi-vehicle trajectory planning, which is a problem in robotics and control systems. The use of Hamilton-Jacobi reachability and sequential trajectory planning methods suggests that the paper falls under the category of Robotics (cs.RO). The paper also deals with adversarial intruders, which suggests that it may also belong to the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The problem of safe and resilient trajectory planning also involves system-level considerations, which suggests that it may belong to the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). The use of algorithms and computational resources suggests that it may also belong to the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA).
